This paper deals with wireless access points on unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and their performance in cellular networks. This topic falls under the category of computer networks and the most relevant sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of coverage probability, which is related to information theory and communication systems, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The use of UAVs for mobile service provisioning involves control and coordination, which can be categorized under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The performance trade-offs discussed in the paper can also be seen as a control problem, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of directional antennas on UAVs for coverage areas can be seen as a multimedia communication problem, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
